technologies and processes it primarily invests in the eastern united states for smaller companies and throughout the united states canada and mexico for larger companies the firm typically invests in companies with revenues between  million and  million and ebitda between  million and  million it will cons stanford investment group inc is a private equity firm specializing in management buyouts corporate divestitures recapitalizations turnarounds pipes and coinvestments in middle market companies the firm seeks to invest in business services healthcare products and services consumable products niche manufacturing logistics industrial outsourcing and disruptive technologies and processes it primarily invests in the eastern united states for smaller companies and throughout the united states canada and mexico for larger companies the firm typically invests in companies with revenues between  million and  million and ebitda between  million and  million it will consider distressed and underperforming companies requiring strategic and operational changes in addition to capital stanford investment group inc was founded in  and is based in new york new york with an additional office in ridgewood new jersey detailed description  avenue of americassuite new york ny united statesfounded in  wwwstanfordinvgroupcom key executives for stanford investment group inc mr david rajpurohit cfa managing partner mr bart klim principal lamont larobordier principal ms nina rajpurohit senior associate mr stephen j berman investment professional compensation as of fiscal year  similar private companies by industry company name region visory llc united states  road partners llc united states t partners llc united states jumpcom inc united states  ontario inc united states recent private companies transactions typedate target no transactions available in the past  months request profile update   the information and data displayed in this profile are created and managed by sp global market i